<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Notes Israeli `Obstacles' to Implementation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1202194294 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 12 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1202194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday, in Tunis, Brother President Abu-'Ammar 
received a troika delegation comprised of the ambassadors of 
Greece, Germany, and Belgium, along with the EC commissioner. 
  Abu-'Ammar briefed the ambassadors on the Cairo document, 
which was signed within the framework of the Gaza-Jericho first 
agreement to advance a just and comprehensive peace in the 
Middle East. He pointed out the obstacles placed by Israel in 
the path of this agreement. Abu-'Ammar impressed on the 
ambassadors the need to urge the Israeli Government to expedite 
the implementation of the Washington agreement and meet its 
target dates. The Israeli side, he emphasized, should show 
credibility and implement the agreements it has signed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

