<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Reaffirms Adherence to `Cultural Course' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1302165794 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 2245 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1302165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The president of the Republic, Lieutenant General 
'Umar al-Bashir, has confirmed the revolution's adherence to the 
cultural course accepted by the Sudanese people of making god's 
law their arbiter. He said that the dogfight of the enemies and 
those lying in wait for us would only make us more determined to 
move forward to establish a good society, a society of values 
and decent morals. 
  Lieutenant General al-Bashir made it clear in his speech 
before the masses during the holding of god's table [ma'idat 
al-rahman ayt -- breaking the fast for the poor] at Umm Baddah 
that the conspiracy of the West will not frighten us, because we 
know that power belongs to god alone. The shortage of funds, 
men and fruits [koranic quote] to which we have been subjected 
is no more than a trial from god to test the extent of our 
adherence to his course and the extent of our turning towards 
him. 
  He stated: We once again declare our rejection of all 
resolutions and charters of the security council and the United 
Nations which contradict god's law. 

</TEXT>

