<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Country Said Ready To Send Troops to Bosnia If Asked </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1002124094 Khartoum SUNA in English 0940 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1002124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 10 Feb (SUNA) -- President of the republic 
General 'Umar al-Bashir has declared Sudan readiness to send 
troops to Bosnia-Hercegovina if the country is asked to do so 
and if the U.N. peacekeeping forces decided to pull out from 
there. 
  Speaking at his regular meeting with the leaderships of the 
national media, General al-Bashir called on the Islamic nations 
to send forces beside the U.N. Forces in Bosnia, adding that the 
threat to withdraw the U.N. troops from Bosnia in the last part 
in the conspiracy targeting the Bosnian people [sentence as 
received]. 
  He added that there is no serious reaction to the agression 
of the Serb forces which have been bombing the civilians in 
Bosnia- Hercegovina. 

</TEXT>

