<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Country To Resume Iran-Egypt Mediation Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1402111094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 13 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1402111094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Well-informed political 
sources said in Cairo yesterday that Damascus is currently 
preparing to make a new move toward Tehran in the framework of 
what was termed as a Syrian move to mediate between Cairo and 
Tehran after an interruption of several months. 
  The sources told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that Syrian President 
Hafiz al-Asad will visit Tehran this month. Meanwhile, it has 
been reported that al-Asad will meet with Egyptian President 
Husni Mubarak this month as well. The political circles said 
that there is a link between the next Syrian move at this level 
and the escalation in Hizballah's activities against Israel via 
southern Lebanon. 
  The sources said that al-Asad will offer new proposals which 
could bring views closer between Cairo and Tehran in a renewal 
of the Syrian endeavor -- which was suspended before the end of 
last year -- to correct positions and ease recent factors of 
tension between them. 
  The sources also said that the Syrian president will submit 
to Iranian President Hashemi-Rafsanjani a report on the 
development of the Arab-Israeli peace negotiations, the results 
of his talks in Geneva last month with U.S. President Bill 
Clinton, and the future of peace in the light of the new factors 
and changes. The sources said that the Syrian move requires 
regional coordination and support in the framework of strategic 
interests. 

</TEXT>

