<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Arrives for 3-Day Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Visit Agenda Detailed </H4>
<F P=102> TA1302173694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 13 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1302173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe has arrived on 
a three-day official visit to Israel. Arriving at Ben-Gurion 
Airport, he was received by Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin. 
Tonight the guest will dine with Foreign Minister Peres, and 
tomorrow the two will hold a working meeting. Also tomorrow, 
Alain Juppe will meet with the prime minister, the president, 
MIA's relatives, and the Likud chairman and visit Yad Vashem 
[holocaust memorial museum]. He is also slated to tour the Gaza 
Strip in the course of his visit. 
  Lord MacKay, the British shipping and aviation secretary 
[title as heard], is also expected in Israel tonight. He is 
accompanied by representatives of British airlines and shipping 
companies, who will discuss joint projects with Israeli 
businessmen. 

</TEXT>

