<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli-PLO Negotiations Resume in Taba </TI></H3>
<H4>   Quray' Comments on Accord </H4>
<F P=102> NC1402135494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1402135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli-PLO talks on the implementation of the 
self-rule plan in Gaza and Jericho resumed in Taba today. 
Disputed security issues were settled by the agreement the two 
sides signed in Cairo last week. 
  Ahmad Quray', Fatah Central Committee member and a key 
Palestinian negotiator, said the Cairo agreement is a genuine 
translation of the Oslo accord. What we have reached on the 
border crossings, he said, was even better than what was reached 
in Oslo. He noted that the Israelis agreed that the Palestinian 
flag be raised over the crossings. 

</TEXT>

