<F P=102>  BK1502161794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1502161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The external affairs minister, Mr. Dinesh Singh, has 
underlined the need for India and the United States to cooperate 
against terrorism for promoting peace. Mr. Dinesh Singh told 
the U.S. senator, Mr. Moynihan, who called on him in New Delhi 
today, that it is also necessary for Pakistan to desist from 
supporting terrorism if it is serious about normalizing 
relations. Both also discussed Indo-U.S. relations and felt 
that the economic relationship is picking up day by day. Mr. 
Moynihan said substantial increase in the U.S. economic 
engagement in India augurs well for the future. 
  The Janata Dal has strongly criticized the U.S. interference 
in India's internal affairs. The national executive of the 
party, in a resolution adopted at its meeting in New Delhi 
today, said that the U.S. attempt to use the Kashmir issue to 
violate Indian sovereignty and Washington's comments on Punjab 
amount to rank interference. 

</TEXT>

