<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PNSF, Fatah Official Criticize Cairo Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1502165094 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1600 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1502165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 15 Feb (SANA)--The Palestinian National 
Salvation Front [PNSF] has warned against the seriousness of the 
Cairo agreement signed by Israel and the PLO. It pointed out 
that this agreement has clearly disclosed the extent of the 
concessions 'Arafat made in the Oslo agreement. 
  In a statement issued today, the PNSF said the articles and 
terms of reference of the Cairo agreement violate national and 
pan-Arab principles. This agreement is a coordinative approach 
with the enemy and an attempt to end our people's intifadah, 
tamper with their security, and liquidate their cause and 
rights, which will threaten our people's existence and national 
destiny. 
  In another development, brother Abu-Musa [Sa'id Musa 
Muragha], secretary of the Fatah Central Committee, said the 
Fatah Movement rejects the Cairo agreement which bestows full 
legitimacy on Israel's occupation of the Gaza Strip and Jericho 
and entrenches the Zionist settlements. 
  In a press statement today, Abu-Musa added: We see in this 
agreement an additional step in a plan hostile to our people and 
nation. This step is intended to generalize the phenomenon of 
the Oslo agreement in the region and penetrate deeper into Arab 
ranks by peddling partial and separate agreements, he noted. 

</TEXT>

