<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Accused of Seeking To Undermine Fatah </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1502200894 Jerusalem AL-QUDS in Arabic 15 Feb 94 pp 1, 18 </F>
<F P=103> TA1502200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-QUDS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Jerusalem, QUDS PRESS -- Fatah, the principal 
faction in the PLO, has accused the Israeli intelligence 
services of launching a "grave and systematic war" with the aim 
of undermining the movement's internal front which supports the 
peace process and the self-rule agreement. [passage omitted] 
  The Fatah statement warned against a war being waged by the 
Shin Bet in a bid to "prepare the climate for a prolonged civil 
war." The statement said that "the Shin Bet aims to create 
suspect bodies that raise the national slogan and operate under 
different names within Fatah." It called on the movement's 
supporters "to act with alertness and high responsibility and 
not deal with these unofficial and illegitimate organizations." 
  The statement stressed that "organizational statements" 
signed by Fatah in the West Bank and Gaza Strip "are approved 
officially by Fatah's supreme organizational committee in the 
occupied territories." Other statements are considered 
"unofficial," including those by "Fatah's organizational offices 
in the territories." 

</TEXT>

