<H3> <TI>   Qaddumi Arrives in Amman for Cooperation Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Committee Concludes Meetings </H4>
<F P=102> JN1602114194 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1100 GMT 
16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1602114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Higher Jordanian-Palestinian Committee has 
concluded the meetings it held in Amman yesterday and today. 
The Jordanian side to the talks was headed by Dr. Sa'id 
al-Tall, deputy prime minister and minister of higher education, 
while the Palestinian side was led by Faruq Qaddumi, head of the 
PLO Political Department. 
  During its meetings, the committee reviewed issues of 
bilateral and Arab concern to promote the overall bilateral 
cooperation and coordination to the required level in all areas. 
The committee also reviewed recent developments in the peace 
process, including the agreement the PLO and Israel signed in 
Cairo on 9 February, which constitutes a major step toward the 
implementation of the Gaza-Jericho accord, which is the first 
part of the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of Principles. 
  The two sides expressed satisfaction with the climate of 
understanding that permeated the talks, something which promotes 
bilateral coordination. This climate also demonstrates the need 
to promote and enhance this coordination in all areas, given 
that it is a realistic response to the special, historical, and 
fateful relationship between the two peoples, as well as a 
response to the common challenges facing them. 

</TEXT>

