<H3> <TI>   Information Minister Receives Japanese Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1402182294 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1700 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1402182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Minister of State for Prime Ministry Affairs and 
Minister of Information Dr. Jawad al-'Anani has received 
Director of the Middle East Affairs Department at the Japanese 
Foreign Ministry (Shiguro Andu). Discussions tackled bilateral 
relations. 
  Dr. al-'Anani reaffirmed Jordan's constant stance towards 
the 
Middle East conflict and the necessity to achieve a just and 
comprehensive settlement as well as resolving all issues on all 
negotiating tracks between the Arab states and Israel. 
  The Japanese official, whose country presides over the 
environment working group at the multilateral talks, praised 
Jordan's role in the Middle East peace negotiations and its 
interest in the environment. He underlined the importance of 
bolstering the existing bilateral ties, particularly in the 
economic and trade fields. 

</TEXT>

