<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Transport Minister Arrives in Khartoum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1502194294 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1405 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1502194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 15 Feb (SUNA) -- Iraqi Minister of 
Transport and Communications Dr. Ahmad Murtada Ahmad Khalil 
arrived in Khartoum yesterday. In a press statement issued 
after his arrival, he said his visit was one of a series between 
the two fraternal countries to discuss various issues. His 
Excellency said that in the field of transport and 
communications, Iraq was fully prepared to cooperate with Sudan 
in railways, sea transport, land transport, civil aviation, as 
well as communications in the interests of the two friendly 
countries. He expressed the hope that the result of his visit 
to Sudan would be fruitful and positive in different fields. 

</TEXT>

