<H3> <TI>   Transport Talks Begin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1502195794 Khartoum SUNA in English 1610 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1502195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 15 Feb (SUNA) -- Meetings of the official 
talks between Sudan and Iraq in the field of transport were 
started here on Tuesday under the co-chairmanship of Iraqi 
Transport Minister Mr. Ahmad Murtada Khalil and Sudanese 
Transport Minister Uthman 'Abd-al-Qadir ['Abd-al-Latif]. 
'Abd-al-Qadir hailed the cooperation between the two countries 
and the Iraqi support to Sudan despite its critical 
circumstances. 
  The Iraqi minister said his visit came as a confirmation of 
the continuous cooperation between the two countries in the 
field of transport and condemned the embargo being committed 
against Sudan and Iraq. He underlined that Iraq realized great 
achievements following the Gulf war in the field of 
rehabilitation and installations. Iraq was looking for more 
cooperation in all fields, he said. 
  The two ministers visited today Khartoum airport and the 
Sudanese Airlines Corporation, where they got acquainted with 
the efforts being made to promote the corporation and the 
cooperation fields. The Iraqi transport minister expressed 
readiness to remove all difficulties facing the corporation. 

</TEXT>

