<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Georgian Foreign Minister Chikvaidze Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502180394 Tehran IRNA in English 1743 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1502180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 15, IRNA -- Georgian Foreign Minister 
Aleksandr Chikvaidze heading a delegation arrived here Tuesday 
and was welcomed by his Iranian counterpart 'Ali Akbar Velayati. 
Upon arrival at the airport he told IRNA that the main purpose 
of his visit was deepening and expansion of bilateral ties and 
cooperation in all areas. He said that during the recent visit 
of the Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze to Iran the two 
countries had reached considerable understandings on light 
industries, machine building mining, and steel mill. 
  Velayati also said that the Georgian embassy in Tehran would 
be inaugurated shortly, and that the future visit of President 
Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani to Tblisi would bring about a basic 
development in the two countries' relations. 
  Iran and Georgia inked eight agreements in economic, 
cultural, commercial, gas, and transportation fields during the 
previous meetings of the two countries officials, which are to 
be followed up during Chikvaidze's visit. 

</TEXT>

