<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Envoy Discusses Kashmir With Larijani </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502181594 Tehran IRNA in English 1630 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1502181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 15, IRNA -- Special envoy of Pakistan's 
prime minister, N.D. Khan, discussed the Kashmir issue with 
Vice-Chairman of the Majles Foreign Relations Committee 
Mohammad-Javad Larijani here Tuesday [15 February]. Khan in the 
meeting said that Pakistan intends to propose a resolution on 
the rights of the Kashmiri Muslims to the future United Nations 
meeting in Geneva. 
  Expressing grave concern over the condition of Muslims in 
Kashmir, he called on the Islamic Republic of Iran to support 
the resolution. 
  Larijani in reply said the Iranian Majles would decisively 
support any efforts aimed at the restoration of Muslims rights 
in Kashmir. Majles is ready to offer constructive views for the 
preparation of a comprehensive and practical resolution in this 
regard, he added. Khan who is visiting several member countries 
of the Organization of the Islamic Conference, also held talks 
on the same issue with chairman of the Majles Human Rights 
Committee Sa'id Raja'i Khorasani later in the day. 

</TEXT>

