<H3> <TI>   Rabin on Lebanon, `Right To Protect' Interests </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1602061994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 16 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1602061994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rabin yesterday disclosed that there 
have been U.S. efforts to ease tensions in southern Lebanon. 
But the premier said Israel reserves the right to protect her 
interests. 
  [Begin Rabin recording] There were American talks with the 
Syrians, with the Lebanese, and with the Israelis. I will not 
elaborate what were in this talks. Israel has explained its 
position: We will continue to act in accordance to our 
decisions what is good, what is needed to achieve peace to the 
Galilee and security to our forces and to the SLA [South 
Lebanese Army] forces in the security zone. I am fully aware 
that Syria could restrain Hizballah, but Syria did it for 10 
days before the Geneva summit meeting between Presidents Clinton 
and al-Asad. Since then we see escalation in the activities by 
Hizballah against our forces in the security zone. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

