<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres Promises Close Supervision of Immigration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1602115294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 16 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1602115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres told the Knesset 
plenum that Israel did not forfeit its right to supervise the 
Palestinians' efforts to encourage illegal immigration in the 
territories. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that Peres 
was responding to queries by several Knesset members claiming 
that the arrangements on the border crossings would allow the 
Palestinians to carry out the right of return. Peres said that 
if the Palestinian leadership violates the agreements Israel 
will implement sanctions, including summarily preventing 
Palestinian entrance by resorting to the right of veto Israel 
was given in the agreement. 
  The foreign minister said that last year approximately 
300,000 Palestinians entered the territories for summer visits. 
He admitted that supervision of their exit at the end of their 
visits is not perfect. 

</TEXT>

