<DOCNO> FBIS3-34892 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes032_l_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-032 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Continues Visit, Meets Palestinians </TI></H3>
<H4>   Juppe Pledges Support to Palestinians </H4>
<F P=102> TA1502124694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1100 GMT 15 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1502124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe met today with 
Palestinian representatives at Orient House in East Jerusalem. 
Following the meeting, Juppe told reporters that France would 
continue to support the peace process. In particular, the 
foreign minister said, France would contribute funds to the 
Palestinians, in addition to the 500 million ECU's already 
pledged by the European Committee. 
  [Begin recording] [Juppe] Yes, we have decided to implement 
a new protocol of 60 million francs in 1994 for the occupied 
territories. [end recording] 
  Palestinian leader Faysal al-Husayni, who attended the 
meeting, told reporters he believed the recent spate of terror 
attacks could be better handled if the Palestinians controlled 
the areas. Al-Husayni agreed that support among Palestinians 
for the peace process had dwindled, but was convinced that 
things could change. 
  [Al-Husayni] There is less support because nothing is 
implemented on the ground. In the moment that there will be 
implementation on the ground, I believe that the Palestinian 
people will support. The Palestinian people stopped to believe 
words and sentences; they would like to see something on the 
ground. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

