<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Continues Visit, Meets Palestinians </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Husayni: Meeting With Juppe `Positive' </H4>
<F P=102> JN1502133094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1100 GMT 15 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1502133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "With the Midday Events" feature] </F>
  [Text] French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe has met with an 
East Jerusalem delegation led by Faysal al-Husayni. Talks dealt 
with the French aid to Palestinians during the forthcoming 
self-rule period. Our correspondent Ahmad 'Ubaydat reports on 
this meeting: 
  [Begin recording] ['Ubaydat] The French Government is 
committed to supporting the peace process and helping the 
Palestinians in all domains in order to successfully establish 
their self-rule. This was stated by French Foreign Minister 
Alain Juppe during his meeting with some Palestinian figures at 
the Palestinian delegation's headquarters today. Juppe said: 
Today's meeting was cordial and positive. As you know, the 
French Government has for long been calling for and supporting 
the idea of direct dialogue between Israel and the PLO. This 
has actually been achieved following the signing of the 
principles agreement and the mutual recognition. The minister 
also discussed France's efforts in this regard, particularly its 
contribution to economic development in the territories. 
  Faysal al-Husayni voiced optimism over this meeting. He 
said: 
  [Al-Husayni] In fact, the meeting was very positive. They 
talked about their clear political position on the peace process 
as a whole and on the issue of Jerusalem. They also expressed 
their readiness to develop the aid extended to us, whether it is 
financial aid or training assistance. 
  ['Ubaydat] The French foreign minister left for the Gaza 
Strip to acquaint himself with the situation there. He will 
then return to Jerusalem. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

