<H3> <TI>   Ramallah Mosque Ordered Closed for Year </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1502112994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 15 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1502112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Security forces ordered the closure for one year of 
a Ramallah mosque in which Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] 
uniforms, head coverings, and instigative material were found. 
The order was approved after it was learned that the mosque 
served as a Hamas base. 
  Students from two Bethlehem schools stoned IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] soldiers, but there were no casualties. The 
students hurled the stones because they failed in their 
matriculation examinations. 
  Police Commissioner Rafi Peled said that the police plan to 
increase supervision of residents from the territories crossing 
the Green Line to work in Israel, and if needed approval of 
entry into Israel will be made tougher. 

</TEXT>

