<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Forces Dialogue Committee Concludes Agenda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1402123794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1402123794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a meeting yesterday in the capital, Sanaa, the 
Political Forces Dialogue Committee concluded its agenda 
regarding preparations for the signing of the accord document 
and guarantees for immediate implementation. 
  In two meetings on Saturday and Sunday [12, 13 February], 
the 
Political Forces Dialogue Committee approved the formation of a 
committee to consider views regarding the necessary security 
guarantees to begin implementation. 
  The Political Forces Dialogue Committee also approved the 
formation of another committee to prepare the necessary 
appendices to the document and draft a statement announcing the 
signing of the document. A third committee will take care of 
protocol arrangements for the signing ceremony, which will be 
held in the Jordanian capital, Amman, on 10 Ramadan, 
corresponding to 20 February, per consultations with the 
brothers in the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan. 
  The Political Forces Dialogue Committee agreed to meet next 
Thursday to see what these committees will come up with and make 
appropriate decisions. 
  The Political Forces Dialogue Committee has said it will 
continue to be in session, in line with the constitutional, 
legal, and procedural guarantees approved by the committee late 
last week. 

</TEXT>

