<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Protests Salih's Order To Cancel South's Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1602073394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0500 GMT 16 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1602073394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It appears that differences between the Yemeni 
president and his deputy have not been completely solved. The 
Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] yesterday issued a statement 
broadcast over Aden radio protesting President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih's order to annul Prime Minister Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas' 
decision to appoint a new governor of the southern (?Abyan) 
Governorate. 
  The YSP, which is led by Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, 
said that al-'Attas' decision does not contravene the 
constitution as long as it aims to prevent corruption in the 
governorate. 
  The Yemeni presidency regarded the decision as a violation 
of 
both the constitution and the law because appointing governors 
must be effected by joint decisions of the president and the 
vice president. 
  It goes without saying that this issue is within the 
differences which seem to be continuing between the northerners 
and southerners, between the president and the vice president, 
or between the two main political parties, the YSP and General 
People's Congress. 

</TEXT>

