<F P=102>  NC1602100394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 16 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1602100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fierce fighting has been raging between resistance 
men, on one hand, and Israeli troops and the agent Lahd militia 
[South Lebanese Army] on the other, along the Zummarayya combat 
line since 0800 today. Artillery and rockets are being used in 
the clashes. 
  A group of resistance men attacked a Lahdist patrol on the 
Hasbani-Zummarayya road this morning. Resistance men also 
pounded Lahdist posts in 'Ayn Qinya. 
  Israeli forces bombarded several southern areas at 0700 
today, including the Mimas axis, Marj al-Zuhur, Mazra'at 'Ayn 
Jabbur, Jabal al-Zahr, and Dallafah. A column of 12 Israeli 
armored vehicles escorted by some 50 troops advanced toward the 
Zummarayya crossing point. 
  Meanwhile, the area between al-Hamra' and Haddathah came 
under fierce attacks amid Israeli overflights today. 

