Arabic 1800 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1402194694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Rebellious Iraq </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Informed sources have said that the tyrant's 
military units have been deployed 3 km from the border strip 
with the State of Kuwait in an area between Umm Qasr and Hafar 
al-Batin. The sources added that Saddam's authorities are now 
beefing up their forces deployed there. The sources said that 
these forces, which consist of armored battalions and artillery 
batteries, are being moved during nighttime from the 
Governorates of al-Nasiriyah and al- Samawah and from major 
points in al-Basrah to the border area with Kuwait. 
  Our sources said that these units, which are mobilized in 
the 
border strip with Kuwait, are affiliated with the elite units of 
the Presidendial Guard which Saddam prepared recently following 
his continuous defeats before the sons of our revolting people. 

