<F P=102>  JN1502152394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1400 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1502152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 15 Feb (INA) -- The Arab Socialist Ba'th 
Party and the Yemeni Revolutionary Democratic Party today signed 
a program of action and cooperation to enhance and cement 
relations of brotherliness, steadfastness, and friendship 
between the two friendly parties and peoples. 
  The program was signed for the Ba'th Party by 'Abd-al-Razzaq 
al-Hashimi, chief of the Ba'th Party's Foreign Relations Bureau, 
and for the Yemeni party by Muhammad 'Abdallah al-Dughaysh, the 
party's secretary general. The program urges coordinating 
efforts at Arab and international forums and conferences and 
educating Arab and world public opinion about the serious, 
tragic effects of the crime of the unjust embargo against the 
Iraqi people and using all means to lift it. 
  The program provides for exchanging visits and expertise to 
ensure continued communication between the two parties in the 
interest of common pan-Arab struggle and the Arab nation's 
objectives of liberation and progress. The program provides for 
supporting the Arab Popular Forces Conference and contributing 
to its activities and decisions. 

</TEXT>

