<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Speaker Meets British War Crimes Committee Member </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1502134294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1130 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1502134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] National Assembly Speaker Sa'di Mahdi Salih, today 
received Hugh Stevens, of the British committee investigating 
international war crimes, who is on a visit to Iraq. 
  Sa'di Mahdi Salih told him the West must understand that the 
Iraqi people, who stood up to the largest aggressive force in 
history, are solidly behind their wise leadership. The Iraqis, 
he emphasized, are determined to defend their country's 
sovereignty, and have confidence in their political choices. 
The Iraqis will not stand for any interference in their own 
affairs. 
  Sa'di Mahdi Salih said the United States is working to 
perpetuate its control over the international community to 
advance its own and Western strategic ambitions in the Arab 
world. He urged the international community to work hard to 
promote better international relations. 
  Mr. Stevens indicated that his visit to Iraq was useful in 
that he was able to see firsthand the Iraqi people's distress 
caused by the relentless sanctions. He was also impressed by 
Iraq's rehabilitation effort to repair the damage wrought by the 
aggression. He will use the information gleaned from his visit 
to Iraq in a political file geared toward British public opinion. 

</TEXT>

