<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Informed of `Further Violations' of Airspace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1502121894 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1115 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1502121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New York, 15 Feb (INA) -- Iraq has informed the 
general secretariat of the United Nations of further violations 
of its airspace by U.S. aircraft for purposes of surveillance 
and provocation and dropping thermal flares. 
  Iraq's permanent UN delegate, in a letter to Secretary 
General Butrus-Ghali, said that from 1 to 10 February, 841 
sorties were conducted over large areas of northern and southern 
Iraq. 
  Two T.S.R.S1 [as received] American reconnaissance planes 
violated Iraq's airspace on 3 and 6 February, flew over 
al-Nasiriyah, al-'Amarah, al-Samawah, al-Jalibah, al-Ratawi, 
Qal'at Sukkar, and (?al-Busayyah), and then headed to Saudi 
Arabia. 
  A hostile plane on 7 February dropped three thermal flares 
over the Ba'shiqah district in the Governorate of Ninawa. 

</TEXT>

