<H3> <TI>   Mujahidin Claim of Attack on Regime Company </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1502171994 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1502171994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic revolution mujahidin have confronted a 
special unit of the regime's security forces known as the 
emergency company. The company was trying to arrest an innocent 
citizen from the area of (al-Sajiyah), which belongs to the 
district of (al-Shifayij) in the governorate of al-Nasiriyah. 
The operation resulted in the killing of the captain who 
commanded the company and two mercenaries. Other people were 
hurt in the operation. One of the vehicles used by the 
attacking force was burned. 
  A group of mujahidin fighters dealt a punitive military blow 
to the headquarters of Saddam's forces in (al-Mudaynah) district 
in the governorate of al-Basrah using 60-mm mortars, hitting 
military locations and the (al-Fathiyah) checkpoint. It also 
killed or wounded regime men. 

</TEXT>

