<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaflets Urging Rebellion Reportedly Distributed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1502164094 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1502164094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thousands of leaflets opposing the regime have been 
distributed during the past few days in the governorates of 
al-Basrah and al-'Amarah and the districts and subdistricts 
belonging to them. These leaflets contain instructions and 
calls to the Iraqi people and Army to rebel against tyrant 
Saddam's regime and to cut off the road before the cliques of 
terrorism and crime that want to destroy Iraq and humiliate its 
people through starvation and oppression. 
  This was revealed by our sources in south Iraq in a report 
in 
which they said that groups of Islamic Resistance men 
distributed revolutionary leaflets in the city of al-Basrah and 
the district of al-Qurnah. The sources added that the biggest 
drop took place at the end of last week. It included the 
district of al-Majarr al-Kabir, Qal'at Salih, al-Maymunah, the 
city of al-'Amarah, and the subdistricts of al-Salam and Nahr 
'Udayl, which belong to the governorate of al-'Amarah. 
  The antiregime leaflets were also distributed in the 
districts of (al-Mudaynah), al-Qurnah, and al-Dayr, the 
subdistricts of al-'Uzayr, (Salhah), and al-Huwayr, and the city 
of al-Basrah, all of which belong to al-Basrah Governorate. 
  Our sources affirmed that the distribution has caused a big 
uproar among the regime's circles. It has forced it to place 
its forces on alert and carry out large-scale search operations 
in these areas and arrest citizens. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

