<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demonstrations Against `Sabotage Cliques' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1402115794 Baghdad AL-'IRAQ in Arabic 11 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1402115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-'IRAQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The residents of the Birah Makrun complex have 
staged a large demonstration in al-Sulaymaniyah Governorate in 
front of the offices of the agent and sabotage cliques. The 
residents demanded redressing their living conditions and daily 
suffering, noting that they have not received food supplies for 
months. In addition, electricity and other basic services are 
absent. 
  Another demonstration was staged at the Shawrash complex in 
Chamchamal District, during which demonstrators demanded 
ensuring food supplies to them. An exchange of fire ensued with 
the demonstrators, prompting the sabotage cliques to close the 
Chamchamal-al-Sulaymaniyah road. 
  Agent and sabotage cliques receive food supplies and then 
sell them on the black market. They are also stealing electric 
wires and transformers and smuggling them across the border, 
thus causing a blanket power cutoff in the region. 

</TEXT>

