<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Arrest Sailor, Seize Arms From Ship </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502193194 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1502193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A statement by the Ministry of Interior and Local 
Authorities discloses that successive investigations have 
enabled the security services to find a quantity of weapons and 
various items which were hidden in an Algerian freighter by the 
sailor Hacene Mialet. His confessions and other clues indicated 
that this equipment was to be delivered to him in the German 
port of Hamburg by Djamel Lounici who is wanted for involvement 
in a number of terrorist activities. 
  An unforeseen event happened and prevented the delivery of 
the equipment at the German harbor, but in the end the weapons 
were delivered to Hacene Mialet in the Belgian port of Antwerp. 
Investigations are continuing and have led to the arrest of 
several people involved including the above-mentioned sailor. 
  The weapons seized are: 20 rifles, 15 automatic pistols, a 
considerable quantity of ammunition, two-way radios, and optical 
equipment. 

</TEXT>

