<F P=102>  NC1302073294 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 0530 
GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1302073294 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [passage omitted] Prime Minister Rafiq 
al-Hariri has affirmed that real preparedness to confront 
developments in the region lies in two basic fields. The first 
is to strengthen and fortify our internal front using all the 
elements needed to destroy divisions among Lebanese. The second 
is to build the establishments of the state in the vital and 
industrial fields and try to develop and confront the 
requirements of the coming stage. 
  Prime Minister al-Hariri's speech came during a seminar held 
in Juniyah yesterday evening. Answering questions from people 
attending the seminar, the prime minister said he supports the 
implementation of al-Ta'if, but the Syrian forces will be 
staying for the time being because they are helping the Lebanese 
security forces preserve internal security. He stressed that 
Lebanon came to the negotiations with Syria and will leave them 
when Syria does. [passage omitted] 
  On relations among the three leaders, the prime minister 
said: We do not differ over the essence, but over the form. 
Differences are natural in a democratic system. On the absence 
of balance in national decision-making due to the absence of 
Christian representation, al-Hariri said the Chamber of Deputies 
was elected within an election law. The current government is 
not responsible for the elections that have already taken place. 
He affirmed that when the time comes to hold new parliamentary 
elections, which will not be soon, then we can rectify the 
representation proportions. 

</TEXT>

