<H3> <TI>   British Parliament Accused of Destabilization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1602205294 Omdurman National Unity Radio in English 1500 
GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1602205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman National Unity Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In their (?focal) efforts to destabilize the 
tranquillity in the Sudan, the British House of Commons is 
holding a meeting today with the so-called Sudanese opposition 
groups approved in the rebel factions. The meeting was called 
by Christian Solidarity, at their national agency in London, 
under the auspices of Baroness Cox. The theme of the meeting is 
to unite all Sudanese opposition abroad, with the aim of 
overthrowing the legitimate government of the transitional 
revolution in the Sudan. The organizers of the meeting have 
rejected the participation of neutral Sudanese and Islamic 
institutions in the meetings, which are being kept secret. In a 
separate development, reliable sources disclosed that a meeting 
of rebel factions earlier had taken place in London, under the 
patronage of the anti-Islam christian association. 

