<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Receive UK War Crimes Commission Member </TI></H3>
<H4>   Popular Forces Official Meets Stevens </H4>
<F P=102> JN1602133694 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1220 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1602133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 16 Feb (INA)--Sa'd Qasim Hammudi, secretary 
general of the Arab Popular Forces Conference, has met with Hugh 
Stevens, member of the British international war crimes 
commission. 
  During the meeting, Hammudi asserted that the continued 
enforcement of the unfair embargo clamped on the Iraqi people is 
a crime against a people who opposed aggression, injustice, and 
slavery. 
  For his part, Stevens condemned the unfair embargo imposed 
on 
Iraq, because it is a violation of all international conventions 
and norms, particularly since Iraq has honored all its 
commitments as enshrined in the relevant international 
resolutions. He noted the unethical conduct practiced against 
Iraq during the war of aggression. 

</TEXT>

