<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Receive UK War Crimes Commission Member </TI></H3>
<H4>   Friendship Group Chief Meets Stevens </H4>
<F P=102> JN1602181094 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1700 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1602181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Latif Nusayyif Jasim, chairman of the Iraqi 
Friendship, Peace, and Solidarity Organization, met today with 
Hugh Stevens, coordinator of the British commission for 
investigating international war crimes. 
  During the meeting, Jasim reviewed the effects of the unjust 
blockade imposed on the Iraqi people in contravention of 
international and humanitarian laws and norms. He reviewed the 
Iraqi people's extensive efforts under the leadership of 
struggler President Saddam Husayn to reconstruct what the evil 
ones have destroyed and to launch the new construction campaign. 
  Latif Nusayyif Jasim urged international organizations and 
honorable individuals in the world to continue their protests 
against the crime of the unjust blockade through activities that 
enhance the Iraqi people's steadfastness in the face of the 
unjust blockade. 
  Praising Iraq's reconstruction of what the aggressors have 
destroyed, Hugh Stevens expressed great admiration for Iraq's 
achievements under the leadership of President Saddam Husayn in 
the face of the aggression. He indicated that such achievements 
would not have been realized had it not for the Iraqi people's 
rallying around their national leadership and love for their 
historic leader. 

</TEXT>

