<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Regime Reportedly Kills, Wounds Baghdad Protesters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1602172794 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1530 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1602172794 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1530 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our sources have reported that more than 2,000 
people staged a demonstration in Madinat al-Thawrah in Baghdad 
on Wednesday morning, 2 February. These sources said that the 
Iraqi regime's security service, intelligence units, special 
security units, Republican Guard, and Army personnel confronted 
the demonstration in the al-Jamaliyah quarter. The 
demonstrators wanted to march to Baghdad. These sources said 
that the regime's personnel used batons to stop and disperse the 
demonstration, killing or injuring dozens of innocent civilians. 

</TEXT>

