<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Clashes in South 16-17 February </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Fierce Fighting' Rages </H4>
<F P=102> TA1602121694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1100 GMT 16 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1602121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] With the Hizballah organization marking the 
second anniversary of an Israel Air Force attack that killed 
local leader Shaykh 'Abbas Musawi, fierce fighting raged in the 
area this morning. The offense began when Hizballah launched 
katyusha rockets at targets in the eastern sector of the south 
Lebanon security zone. Most landed in open areas without causing 
either injuries or damage, with Hizballah continuing the attack 
with RPG antitank rockets. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] and 
SLA [South Lebanese Army] hit back with tank fire, and according 
to Lebanese radio reports battle helicopters strafed the area of 
Kafr Shuba in the security zone, while war planes patrolled the 
skies. 
  Other areas hit by RPG, machine-gun fire, and light weapons 
fire were al-Hamra' bridge in the western sector, and around 
Marj 'Uyun. Shaykh Musawi, one of the most prominent Hizballah 
leaders in the south, died when his car was hit by Israeli 
helicopter fire near his home in Jibshit. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

