<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Clashes in South 16-17 February </TI></H3>
<H4>   2 UN Officers Wounded by Mine </H4>
<F P=102> TA1702085894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 17 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1702085894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two UN officers were wounded this morning when they 
stepped on an antipersonnel mine in southern Lebanon. The two 
were patrolling north of al-Naqurah when one of them stepped on 
the mine. He was seriously injured, while his colleague received 
minor injuries. They are being treated at the UN Interim Force 
in Lebanon hospital at al-Naqurah. 

</TEXT>

