<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-033 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Clashes in South 16-17 February </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on Fighting </H4>
<F P=102> NC1702103994 (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic 0945 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1702103994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our correspondent in western al-Biqa' reports that 
the villages of Mimis, Marj al-Zuhur, Qilya, and al-Dallafah 
came under heavy machine-gun fire from Israeli Army and South 
Lebanese Army [SLA] positions in Zummarayya and Kawkaba at 0800 
today. At 0830, a SLA force carried out a sweep along the 
Hasbani-Zummarayya road. A general alert was declared among the 
Lebanese Army troops in the Marj al-Zuhur area, Mashgharah, 'Ayn 
al-Tinah, Qilya, and Mimis. At 0900, Israeli helicopters flew 
for 15 minutes over Kawkaba, Marj 'Uyun, and al-'Urqub. 
  Our correspondent in Tyre reports that the Israeli forces at 
dawn today fired 14 mortar shells at the outskirts of al-Mansuri 
and carried out a large-scale sweep in the fields and valleys 
near the village, causing material damage. The resistance 
responded by firing Katyusha rockets at the al-Bayyadah position. 
  Our correspondent in Tyre also reported that two UN officers 
have been injured by a land mine in the Shama' area, in the 
western sector of the border strip. 

</TEXT>

