<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab Shot Dead by Soldiers; Another Wounded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1702095994 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0930 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1702095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Arab resident of Misilyah, south of Janin, was 
shot dead by soldiers. Our correspondent in the territories 
Golan Yokhpaz reports that the soldiers, who were stationed at a 
roadblock in the village, detained the man in order to carry out 
a routine check of his papers. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
is currently investigating why one of the soldiers shot the 
local resident. 
  A young Arab was slightly wounded in the leg this morning 
when shot by soldiers in Halhul after he stoned an IDF patrol. 
Halhul and Hebron residents rioted following yesterday's 
killing of a Halhul resident by soldiers. 
  Our correspondent reports that there is a general strike 
today in most major towns in Judaea and Samaria in solidarity 
with Palestinian prisoners in Israeli jails. 

</TEXT>

