<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   NRP, Tzomet Party Discuss Joining Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1302203494 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1302203494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In the wake of Labor Secretary General Nisim 
Zvili's remarks about a Palestinian state, NRP [National 
Religious Party] and Tzomet officials said today that it is 
preferable to influence the government policy from within the 
government, rather than through demonstrations and protests. 
There is talk in these parties about joining the government 
following the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] withdrawal from Gaza 
and Jericho. Minister Ya'aqov Tzur is liaising between the 
Labor and these parties. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

