<DOCNO> FBIS3-35021 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes033_m_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-033 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Prime Minister Arrives for Signing Ceremony </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1702113894 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 17 Feb 94 pp 1, 22 </F>
<F P=103> JN1702113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] As of today, Amman will witness an extensive 
political move to prepare in various fields for the historic 
reconciliation meeting to be held in Amman on Sunday, 20 
February, which will bring together Yemeni President 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. During 
the meeting, the Yemeni document of pledge and accord will be 
signed to mark the end of the political crisis and entrenchment 
of Yemeni unity. 
  Within the framework of the signing ceremony, Mujahid 
Abu-Shawarib, Yemeni deputy prime minister and head of the 
Yemeni reconciliation meeting team, arrived in Amman yesterday. 
  A high-level Yemeni media and political delegation is 
scheduled to arrive in Amman early this morning in order to 
prepare for Sunday's reconciliation meeting to be held under the 
auspices of His Majesty King Husayn. 
  The delegation is led by Salim Salih Muhammad, member of the 
Yemeni Presidential Council, and comprises members of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party's Central Committee and Political Bureau. 
  Ahmad Jabir 'Afif, head of the Yemeni Political Forces 
Dialogue Committee said that President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, members of the Dialogue 
Committee, and top political and social figures representing the 
main Yemeni parties are expected to arrive in Amman on Sunday, 
20 February, in preparation for signing the accord document in 
Amman of the Arabs. 
  In a telephone conversation with AL-DUSTUR, 'Afif said that 
everything on the Yemeni side is ready, that all matters are 
proceeding in the right direction, and that all efforts are 
being made to travel to Amman on 10 Ramadan, corresponding to 20 
February, to meet with His Majesty King Husayn and to sign the 
document. 
  'Afif reiterated the Yemeni people's eagerness to maintain 
their unity, stability, and security. He noted that unity 
exists and that it is the right of the Yemeni people, who insist 
on maintaining this unity whatever the circumstances. 
  'Afif said that His Majesty King Husayn's role has greatly 
helped reconcile the parties and restore amity due to the great 
respect and appreciation the Yemeni president, vice president, 
and all the Yemeni people have for his majesty. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

