<H3> <TI>   Jordanian-Palestinian Committee Concludes Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-'Anani Calls For Jerusalem Committee </H4>
<F P=102> JN1602193394 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 
GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1602193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Higher Jordanian-Palestinian Committee 
concluded its meetings at the Foreign Ministry today and issued 
a joint statement on these meetings. Details are in the 
following report from our correspondent for political affairs, 
Shakir Maharimah: 
  [Begin recording] [passage omitted] [Maharimah] Information 
Minister Dr. Jawad al-'Anani, a member of the Jordanian team, 
responded to questions from journalists on the committee 
meetings. Responding to a question on a Jerusalem committee, 
al-'Anani said: 
  [Al-'Anani] We had to confront what is taking place in 
Jerusalem and to discuss the Palestinian side's ability to 
negotiate it. Therefore, we agreed that the issue of Jerusalem 
is a major and sensitive one. It deserves a specialized 
committee to follow up all aspects of this subject and to try to 
prevent what is taking place inside the city, such as the 
erosion of property inside the walls and the growing settlement 
process in and around it. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

