<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Forms Committee To Resist Normalization </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1702102094 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 17 Feb 94 p 24 </F>
<F P=103> JN1702102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The formation of a Jordanian popular committee for 
the resistance of submission to and normalization with the 
Zionist enemy was announced yesterday. The decision to form the 
committee was announced at the end of a meeting held at the 
headquarters of the Jordanian Arab Socialist Ba'th Party on 27 
January 1994. Seventy-five political, party, and independent 
key figures attended the meeting at the invitation of the 
nationalist Jordanian political parties. After several 
meetings, the temporary committee agreed on the final draft of 
regulations and bylaws. These will be presented to the general 
committee for approval and implementation. 
  In a statement issued yesterday, the temporary committee 
demanded the formation of a broad Jordanian popular movement, 
including all those who stand against the agreements of 
submission and normalization with the Zionist enemy, to work as 
one team to secure the success of the confrontation plan which 
expresses the Arab Jordanian people's rejection of capitulation. 

</TEXT>

