<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Discouraging' Climate of Resumed Talks Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1702094394 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 0545 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1702094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] Under the headline "The Israeli Illusion," 
AL-THAWRAH writes: The Washington talks have resumed on the 
level of the heads of delegations amid discouraging atmospheres. 
Israel is still barricading itself behind its futile ideas and 
continues to put spokes in the wheel of the peace process. 
  The paper stresses that Israel is not only avoiding decisive 
answers on the substance of the peace process regarding the 
question of complete withdrawal, but also proposes absurd ideas, 
which constitute an attempt to escape forward. This is 
especially the case after it was pushed into a difficult dilemma 
by the Syrian position and the Geneva summit. Israel now does 
not have the chance to avoid, for very long, these answers. 
  AL-THAWRAH concludes by saying: Despite the ability it was 
provided by the Oslo and Cairo agreements with the PLO to 
promote separate solutions, Israel will be very mistaken if it 
thinks it can subjugate Syria and the other tracks to separate 
deals which it can tailor to fit its economic, military, 
political, and security interests. Peace, as Syria has always 
said, must be just and comprehensive or else there will be no 
peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

