<H3> <TI>   Katyusha Causes `Light Damage' in Galilee </TI></H3>
<H4>   Commander Blames Palestinians </H4>
<F P=102> TA1602203794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 2030 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1602203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A katyusha rocket was fired today from Lebanese 
territory at the Western Galilee. No one was hurt, but light 
damage was caused to one of the factories in the area. Our 
correspondent in the north Menahem Horowitz reports that this is 
the first katyusha to hit the Galilee since Operation 
Accountability and the understandings made with the Hizballah in 
its wake. 
  [In live telephone update, Yo'av Aviv reports on Qol 
Yisra'el 
in Hebrew at 2030 GMT that "Major General Yitzhaq Mordekhay, 
commander of the Northern Command, this evening confirmed that a 
katyusha hit the Galilee. Gen. Mordekhay believes that the 
missile was fired by Palestinian elements who wish to heat up 
the border area. He said that he holds a grave view of the 
firing."] 

</TEXT>

