<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   General People's Congress Approves New Shari'ah Laws </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1702221294 Tripoli Libyan Television Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1702221294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Libyan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] To be rightly guided by the Holy Koran as the law of 
the new Jamahiri society, the General People's Congress has [in 
its January session in Surt] formulated seven laws that the 
Basic People's Congresses decided in regard to the application 
of Islamic law [shari'ah]: 
  1. The law on purification [al-tatthir] 
  2. The law on retribution and blood money. 
  3. The law on rules of the will. 
  4. The law on prohibition of alcohol. 
  5. The law amending the law on the punishment of theft and 
[word indistinct] 
  6. The law on protecting society from things prohibited by 
the Holy Koran. 
  7. The law amending provisions of the law of marriage and 
divorce and their consequences. 

</TEXT>

