<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paper Lauds Cairo's New Antiterrorist Policy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1802103894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0701 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1802103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 18 Feb (MENA)--The newspaper AL-AHRAM asserts 
that the security forces' recent preemptive strikes against the 
terrorist groups are an indication of a new, successful security 
policy that aims to keep the initiative in the hands of the 
police and deny the terrorists the chance of lying low until it 
is time to perpetrate a new crime. 
  In its editorial today, the paper says that the new security 
policy is based on the availability of accurate and specific 
data about the terrorist organizations, their operational 
methods, hideouts, and modes of communication with each other in 
Egypt and with their financiers and instigators abroad. 
  The paper adds: The facts prove beyond a shadow of doubt 
that these unbalanced young men, devoid of any true religious 
faith, have consciously or unconsciously become agents of 
foreign anti-Egypt schemes to undermine the country's successful 
economic reform program. 
  The paper concludes: Now that the picture is perfectly clear 
and the identities of the murderers known, there is no 
alternative to an all-out confrontation using the law's sharp 
scalpel to excise this malignant tumor from the homeland's body. 

</TEXT>

