<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Sentenced to Death for Plot To Kill Mubarak </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1802112494 Paris AFP in English 1027 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1802112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Feb 18 (AFP)--Three soldiers linked to 
Islamic militants have been condemned to death and three others 
jailed for 10 years for plotting to assassinate Egyptian 
President Husni Mubarak, court sources disclosed Friday. 
  The military court of Sidi Barrani, near the Libyan border, 
passed the death sentence against a second lieutenant in the 
reserves, Midhat Tahawi, and two conscripts, Hamadah Muhammad 
Lutfi and Muhammad Ahmad Sa'id Salih, on Wednesday. 
  One of the conscripts was among the seven Islamic militants 
killed in a police raid on the Cairo district of al-Zawiyah al- 
Hamra' in early February, according to an informed source. The 
other two appeared in court. 
  Another second lieutenant, Fathi Mahmud Khattab, and two 
more 
conscripts were each sentenced to 10 years of hard labour. 
  The court said the six soldiers had planted explosives at 
Sidi Barrani airport and planned to detonate the bomb during a 
visit by Mubarak, who often meets his Libyan counterpart 
Mu'ammar al- Qadhdhafi in the border town. 
  The trial opened on January 30 behind closed doors. 
  The latest verdicts raised to 43 the number of Islamic 
militants sent to death row since October 1992. Twenty-nine 
people have been executed over the last nine months. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

