<H3> <TI>   Minister on Dinar Use in Palestinian `Entity' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1502152894 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 15 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1502152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Amjad Mu'alla] </F>
  [Text] Finance Minister Sami Qammuh has said continued use 
of the Jordanian dinar in the occupied territories after 
establishment of the Palestinian entity will not affect its 
value, but will keep the dinar strong and stable. 
  Answering questions posed by journalists yesterday, Qammuh 
said the stability of the dinar inside and outside Jordan is 
guaranteed by the foreign currency cover. 
  He expressed the hope that coordination and cooperation in 
all fields will continue between Jordan and the Palestinian 
entity in the future. 
  Qammuh held a news conference at the Customs Department in 
which he explained all aspects of the implementation of the 
sales tax and its impact on the Jordanian economy and citizens. 

</TEXT>

