<H3> <TI>   Rabin: Katyusha Fired by Splinter Fatah Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1702164094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1605 GMT 17 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1702164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin says the katyusha that 
fell on the Galilee was fired by a marginal organization. Our 
correspondent Shmu'el Tal reports from the broadcast van at the 
Labor Party building: 
  [Begin recording] [Tal] The Labor Party Bureau is today 
addressing many issues. Among other things, Prime Minister 
Rabin was asked about the katyusha attack in the north. Rabin 
said this attack was contrary to all the understandings attained 
in the wake of Operation Accountability. He noted, however, 
that there was no basic change in the situation: 
  [Rabin] Our understandings with Syria regarding Hizballah 
remain in effect. Today we know the katyusha was launched by a 
splinter Palestinian group that seceded from Fatah due to its 
opposition to the Declaration of Principles in particular and to 
the peace process in general. We will operate as we deem 
necessary. This organization calls itself the Black 13 September 
Organization -- this does not refer to the 13th of September 
1970, but rather to 1993. I believe that this is a marginal 
organization that does not even approximate the magnitude of 
threat posed by Hizballah. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] will 
find the appropriate way to deal with this issue. 
  [Tal] Referring to Syria, Rabin said the ball is now in its 
court. Progress depends not only on Israel, but on Syria as 
well. 
  [Rabin] Why is there no progress? Because Syria poses 
demands we cannot accept. We must adhere to our positions, and 
if Syria wants peace it must adjust to our demands and meet us 
halfway. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

