Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a telephone interview with MBC today, Israeli 
Defense Ministry Spokesman (Odet Ben'ami) said the Palestinian 
Black 13 September Organization [as heard] fired a Katyusha 
rocket at northern Israel last night. He blamed Syria and 
Lebanon on the grounds that Syria controls most of Lebanon and 
that all the activities of Hizballah and other organizations are 
carried out under its supervision, as he put it. 
  Black September broke away from the Fatah Movement after the 
signing of the Oslo accord in September. It is led by Colonel 
Munir Maqdah, who is currently in Lebanon. 
  In contacts with MBC this evening, a Syrian source rejected 
Israel's charge that Damascus is responsible for firing the 
Katyusha rocket at the Galilee. He emphasized that it is not 
Syria's task to guarantee protection for Israel. 

