<H3> <TI>   Settlers Claim Peres Pledged Refugee Return </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1502114794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1100 GMT 15 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1502114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Former Tehiya Knesset Member Elyaqim Ha'etzni 
says the YESHA' [Hebrew acronym for Judaea, Samaria, and Gaza] 
settlers council has received intelligence information that 
Foreign Minister Peres made verbal promises to Yasir 'Arafat 
during the Oslo talks to admit 300,000 Palestinian refugees and 
to start the process of dismantling the settlements. 
  The YESHA' Council yesterday decided to draw up a list of 
volunteers who will be available at short notice to physically 
resist the evacuation of settlements. The move followed 
comments by Foreign Minister Peres questioning the viability of 
the Gaza Strip settlement of Netzarim. [passage omitted] 

