<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Portuguese Foreign Minister Arrives on 2-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1702115494 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 17 Feb 94 p A9 </F>
<F P=103> TA1702115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITIM report] </F>
  [Text] Portuguese Foreign Minister Jose Durao Barroso 
arrived in Israel yesterday afternoon for a two-day visit, his 
first to this country. 
  Upon his arrival, Barroso said he is closely involved in the 
Middle East peace process and noted that he had conferred with 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres during the latter's visit to 
Portugal and with Yasir 'Arafat. 
  According to Barroso, the purpose of his visit is to deepen 
relations between Israel and Portugal in political, economic, 
trade, and tourism spheres. Upon his arrival yesterday, Barroso 
stated that Portugal and Israel will also deepen their cultural 
ties. 
  Yehuda Milo, assistant director general of the Foreign 
Ministry, who greeted Barroso at the airport, said that there is 
fruitful cooperation between the defense industries of Israel 
and Portugal and that the two countries are now working on a 
cooperation agreement in the area of science and development. 
The agreement may be ready to be signed when Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin visits Lisbon next week. 
  Barroso was scheduled to confer with President 'Ezer Weizman 
last night and later to dine with Minister Peres. Today the 
Portuguese foreign minister will hold a working session with his 
Israeli counterpart, confer with the prime minister, and tour 
the Yad Vashem Holocaust Memorial Museum. He will also be 
briefed on the region by a senior Army officer. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

