<H3> <TI>   Ban on Kashmir Group Extended; 5 Killed in Clash </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1802035694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1802035694 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The government has decided to extend the ban on the 
militant outfit, JKLF [Jammu and Kashmir Liberation Front], for 
another two years. The step has been taken under the Unlawful 
Activities Prevention Act. The JKLF was declared an unlawful 
organization by a notification of the Home Ministry two years 
ago. 
  In the Kashmir Valley, four hard-core militants belonging to 
an outlawed outfit were killed in an encounter with the Army 
near Tangmarg in Baramula District yesterday. A spokesman of 
the Defense Ministry said in Srinagar that one Army jawan 
[soldier] was also killed in the encounter. 

</TEXT>

