Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India today warned Pakistan that the process of 
bilateral dialogue will suffer a serious setback if Islamabad 
moves its resolution on Kashmir at the UN Human Rights 
Commission in Geneva. An External Affairs Ministry spokesman 
said in New Delhi today that the whole world knows that 
Pakistan's only intention is to get political gains out of it. 
He said India is committed to resolve all the outstanding 
issues,including Kashmir, through mutual consultations with 
Pakistan. The spokesman said New Delhi is in touch with the 
permanent members of the UN Security Council on the development. 

