<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Results Given for Rajya Sabha Elections in 4 States </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1702163994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1702163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In the biennial elections to the Rajya Sabha, 
the Congress-I has bagged all the four seats from Karnataka, 
while the ruling Left Front has gotten all the five seats in 
West Bengal. Out of the eight seats in Bihar, the Congress-I 
has gotten two, the Janata Dal, 4; and the CPI [Communist Party 
of India] and the BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] one each. The 
lone seat in Sikkim has gone to the Sikkim Sangram Parishad. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

