<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   BJP Assails Clinton Remarks on Rights in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1702154994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1702154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] has criticized 
President Clinton's statement on human rights in Kashmir and 
said it violated diplomatic norms. In a statement, the party 
president, Mr. L.K. Advani, said Mr. Clinton's reference to 
Kashmir constitutes an unwarranted interference in India's 
internal affairs. He said the recent statements of U.S. 
Administration show that it seeks to dismember India. He urged 
the government to convey the nation's sentiments against such 
utterances which will embolden terrorists aided by Pakistan. 

</TEXT>

