<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dallul: Army Mobilized, Ready To Play Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1702141194 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1230 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1702141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Muhsin Dallul has emphasized that 
the problem with Israel is a political not a security one as 
Israel claims. 
  He said: They ask us to halt the resistance so that the 
Israeli army may live on our land, which is foolishness. Our 
land is occupied and the resistance was not the cause of 
occupation but rather a result. 
  He indicated that the army can ensure security in the south 
and if Israel withdraws, the army can carry out security duties 
efficiently. 
  On preparations to face any aggression, he said: We want to 
keep the people steadfast. The resistance will not be touched 
and the army is mobilized and completely ready to play its role 
as it did in the Seven-Day War. These are the capabilities that 
we will use and that we are not willing to surrender. We have 
taken all precautions within our reach and will not give in. He 
added: We are not willing to be defeated peacefully at the 
negotiating table because we were not defeated militarily in the 
war with Israel. Israel should make a decision on a 
comprehensive, just peace and on the exchange of land for peace, 
because occupation and peace cannot be combined. 

</TEXT>

