<H3> <TI>   Tension in South Amid `Enemy' Reinforcements </TI></H3>
<H4>   Agent Militia Said Forcing Enlistment </H4>
<F P=102> NC1702154894 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1230 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1702154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Acute tension and caution prevail in the south and 
western al-Biqa' amid continuing enemy reinforcements and 
threats. 
  Israeli radio said intermittent firing took place between 
the 
Resistance men and the occupation forces and agents. The 
militia [South Lebanese Army, SLA] radio said a Katyusha rocket 
fell at the al-Bayyadah post. 
  The Agent militia continue to force residents of the Strip 
to 
enlist in their ranks. Reports indicate that the militia 
personnel raided Kafr Kila, al-Tayyibah, and al-Qantarah and 
arrested 80 young men aged from 18 to 35 and herded them to a 
training camp in al-Majidiyah. 
  The agent militia commander, Antoine Lahd, has been absent 
recently and his deputy Karamallah Sa'id represents him at 
various meetings and activities. 
  Elsewhere, two officers of the UN Interim Force in Lebanon 
[UNIFIL] were wounded this morning in a landmine explosion while 
on a field tour north of al-Naqurah. They were taken to the 
UNIFIL hospital in al-Naqurah. One of the officers was said to 
be seriously injured and the other slightly. 

