<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tension in South Amid `Enemy' Reinforcements </TI></H3>
<H4>   Israel Reportedly Sends Reinforcements </H4>
<F P=102> NC1802073694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0530 GMT 18 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1802073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guarded calm prevails in the liberated areas in the 
south and western al-Biqa'. However, the massing of Israeli 
troops in the border strip is continuing. According to 
information from the occupied border strip, in the past 12 hours 
Israel brought in about 20 armored vehicles and about 100 troops 
to the areas of al-Khiyam and al-Ahmadiyah, overlooking the 
western al-Biqa'. 

</TEXT>

