<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Briefed on `Financial Balance' Measures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1702204994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1215 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1702204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This morning, the People's Assembly held session a 
under Speaker 'Abd-al-Qadir Qaddurah. At the beginning of the 
session, a summary of deputies' written queries was read out, 
and then referred to competent authorities through the Prime 
Ministry. The assembly then listened to the government's 
responses to deputies' written queries to the Ministry of 
Economy and Foreign Trade on the government's measures 
concerning the dollar exchange rate. The ministry explained 
that the government has adopted a number of measures, including 
the creation of a neighboring market [al-suq al-mujawirah], 
referring many commercial and noncommercial transactions to this 
new market, and encouraging exports and permitting [exporters] 
to keep part of export revenue. The ministry also explained 
measures to combat smuggling and to effect a financial balance 
through increasing revenues and rationalizing expenditure, which 
would include a reconsideration of subsidies for some 
commodities and institutions. The ministry also explained the 
reasons behind the slight rise that occurred in the foreign 
currency exchange rates. 
  Dr. Muhammad al-'Imadi, minister economy and foreign trade, 
explained some points concerning a number of questions. The 
session was adjourned and will reconvene at 1200 Saturday, 26 
February. 

</TEXT>

