<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary: Nothing Left for Palestinians To Negotiate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1802084694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1830 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1802084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed commentary from the "Palestine" program] </F>
  [Text] Arab and non-Arab observers wonder what is left for 
the PLO negotiator to the Taba talks to accept or reject. The 
fact of the matter is that it is Israel that decides and 
dictates agreements between the two parties. If the Palestinian 
negotiator ever defies what is being dictated on him, the matter 
is referred to Yasir 'Arafat, Yitzhaq Rabin, or Shim'on Peres. 
'Arafat will then announce his approval of the arrangements 
Israel wants. 
  Thus, political and media observers began to see, day in and 
day out, further concessions made by the PLO delegation. They 
have now reached the conclusion that Israel has taken 
everything. But, despite this, Israel is exercising further 
extortion just for the sake of it. 
  Israel stuck to its position over passages; settlements and 
the lands around them; main roads; control over the land, sea, 
and air border points; the right to enter the self-rule area to 
arrest wanted Palestinians; and all the other conditions of 
colonialism, hegemony, and tutelage. So what remains to be 
negotiated in Taba? This is the question being asked by 
political observers and world journalists. It is also the 
question which the Palestinian Arab masses are asking. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

