<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Velayati, Pakistani Envoy Discuss Kashmir Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1702044594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0100 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1702044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Professor N.D. Khan, Prime Minister Ms. Benazir 
Bhutto's special envoy, met Iranian Foreign Minister `Ali Akbar 
Velayati, in Tehran yesterday. He stressed the need for 
continuing international pressure on India to stop the 
atrocities on Kashmiris. He said that Pakistan, through 
bilateral dialogue, had tried to persuade India to adopt an 
appropriate posture on the Kashmir issue. Pakistan, however, 
felt that it is India's strategy to take time to suppress the 
legitimate demands of the Kashmiri people. He said that Prime 
Minister Benazir Bhutto has decided to present a resolution at 
the current session of the Human Right Commission meeting in 
Geneva. He expressed the hope that the world community will 
raise its voice against the Indian atrocities in Kashmir. The 
Iranian foreign minister assured the envoy of continued support 
to Pakistan's efforts to stop the human rights violations being 
committed by India and improve the human rights situation in 
Kashmir. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

