<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistan Supported on Kashmir Stand </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK1702163794 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1702163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Iranian President `Ali Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani has 
said Iran fully supports Pakistan's stand on the Kashmir issue. 
Speaking to the Pakistani prime minister's special emissary, 
Professor N.D. Khan, in Tehran today, the Iranian president said 
Pakistan can trust Iran for its support on the Kashmir issue not 
only at the UN Human Rights Commission in Geneva but in other 
organizations as well. He said Iran is fully aware of the 
plight of the Muslims in occupied Kashmir. 
  Earlier, the special emissary handed over to the Iranian 
president a letter from Ms. Benazir Bhutto, appealing for Iran's 
support for Pakistan's resolution to be moved at the Human 
Rights Commission to express concern over the human rights 
violations in occupied Kashmir. Prof. N.D. Khan also apprised 
the Iranian leader of the Indian atrocities in occupied Kashmir 
and told him that India refuses to take steps to halt these 
atrocities. He also thanked Iran for its traditional and solid 
support on the Kashmir stand. 

</TEXT>

