<H3> <TI>   Georgian Foreign Minister Affairs Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Delivers Message to President </H4>
<F P=102> LD1602154694 Tehran IRNA in English 1430 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1602154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 16, (IRNA) -- The visiting Georgian 
minister of foreign affairs, Aleksandre Chikvaidze, here 
Wednesday [16 February] delivered a written message from 
President Eduard Shevardnadze to his Iranian counterpart Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 
  In a meeting with President Rafsanjani, the minister also 
underlined the significance of friendship and neighbourly 
relations between Georgia and the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  Chikvaizde said that in the light of the existing political 
undestanding between the two countries, Tbilisi is ready to 
expand bilateral relations in trade and economic areas. 
  He briefed Rafsanjani on the latest developments in Georgia 
and voiced his country's interest to buy Iranian gas. 
  President Rafsanjani referred to the Geographic situation of 
Georgia in the Caucasus and voiced satisfaction with restoration 
of peace and stability in the republic. 
  He also welcomed consolidation of Tehran-Tbilisi relations 
and said that transfer of Iranian gas would be possible after 
expert studies in the area. 

</TEXT>

