<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Georgian Foreign Minister Affairs Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Majles Official </H4>
<F P=102> LD1702114894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1702114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the meeting in Tehran between Georgian Foreign 
Minister Aleksandr Chikvaidze and Majles Deputy Speaker Rowhani, 
the two sides exchanged views on issues of interest to both 
countries and stressed the need for sincere cooperation among 
the nations of the region. 
  Rowhani referred to the issue of cooperation between the 
Caspian Sea littoral states and said: The countries of this 
region are able to resolve their own issues and do not need the 
presence of foreigners. He also stressed the importance of 
diplomatic solutions for ending the present disputes and 
declared the readiness of the Islamic Republic of Iran to 
mediate in Georgia's internal disputes. 
  The Georgian foreign minister, in turn, referred to the 
existing situation in his country and the parties involoved in 
the dispute, as well as to Georgia's decision to improve its 
relations with the countries of the region. He said: Expansion 
of ties with a large and strong country such as Iran is a cause 
for pride. He then alluded to the historial and cultural bonds 
between the two countries, and expressed the willingess of 
Georgia to further broaden its relations with the Islamic 
Republic of Iran and benefit from Iran's parliamentary 
experiences. 

</TEXT>

