<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Secretary Expresses Thanks for Tajik Mediation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1602195394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1602195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Romero Piriz Ballon, special representative of the 
UN secretary general in Tajikistan affairs, met Foreign Minister 
Velayati today and handed him a written message from the UN 
secretary general for Hashemi-Rafsanjani. Ballon said: The UN 
secretary general has asked me to covey his appreciation and 
thanks to your government for the Islamic Republic of Iran's 
constructive efforts and the positive and worthy role in 
resolving the Tajikistan crisis. 
  In response, Velayati said: The Islamic Republic of Iran has 
always followed Tajikistan issues with concern, and we have 
always believed that a resolution of the Tajik crisis is only 
possible through negotiation and peaceful means. The Islamic 
Republic of Iran will support any move which guarantees 
honorable peace and tranquillity and the rights of all 
interested parties. 

</TEXT>

