<H3> <TI>   Algeria Asks al-Asad To Mediate With Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1702161094 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 17 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1702161094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salwa al-Ustuwani: "Zeroual Asks al-Asad To </F>
Mediate To End Tension Between Iran and Algeria"] 
  [Text] Damascus -- Diplomatic sources in Damascus have 
revealed to AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that Algerian President Liamine 
Zeroual has asked Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad to mediate with 
Iran to end the tension in Algerian-Iranian relations. 
  The sources said that this request came in a message which 
an 
Algerian envoy, namely presidential court director Mohamed 
Sa'idi, delivered to President al-Asad from President Zeroual 
last week. 
  The Syrian sources said that the message dealt with 
conditions in Algeria and bilateral relations, and offered 
condolences to President al-Asad on the loss of his son, Basil 
al-Asad. 
  The sources expects a summit to be held between President 
al-Asad and Iranian President Hashemi-Rafsanjani to discuss 
regional issues, relations between Iran and some Arab states, 
the peace process, and issues of common concern. 
  However, the sources did not say whether the meeting will be 
held in Damascus or Tehran. 

</TEXT>

