<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief Calls For Water Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1702140594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1702140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 
'Abd-al-Majid has again called for convening an Arab conference 
on water immediately within the framework of the Arab League. 
The conference should include the countries directly concerned 
with this problem and other concerned countries that want to 
participate in it so as to define the future strategy of Arab 
water security within the framework of Pan-Arab security. In a 
lecture he delivered yesterday evening at the Egyptian 
University of International Law in Cairo, he said that 
international developments, major economic challenges, and giant 
cartels that have begun to form in the world require the Arab 
countries to take action quickly and to enhance their solidarity 
and cooperation to be able to deal with these challenges and 
blocs strongly and effectively. 

</TEXT>

