<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly, Minister Condemn UN Rights Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1702215694 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 0430 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1702215694 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Transitional National Assembly has condemned the 
report on Sudan presented by the rapporteur of the UN Human 
Rights (?Committee), Gaspar Biro, which described Islamic law 
and punishment as contradictory to UN charters and incompatible 
with human rights. The assembly asked the UN secretary general 
to (?withdraw) the report immediately because it brought into 
disrepute the faith of the Islamic nation. It was a flagrant 
challenge to all divine religions and human values and 
destructive to human rights and international charters. 
  In a report on this matter, the Assembly called on all 
parliaments in Arab and Islamic states and others which respect 
human rights and values to decisively reject this defamation. 
  Meanwhile, Mr. 'Abd-al-Aziz Shiddu, justice minister and 
attorney general, stressed that Gaspar Biro's report is clearly 
a conspiracy against [words indistinct] the West's design to 
destroy Islam and all other divine religions. He said the 
report had a secular base which called for the separation of 
religion and the state and used the United Nations as a tool to 
achieve this. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

