<H3> <TI>   Committee Topics Detailed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2102194494 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2102194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The PLO is seeking Israeli consent to the entry 
of its intelligence and police officers into the Gaza Strip and 
Jericho prior to the Israeli evacuation. Our Arab affairs 
correspondent Ehud Ya'ari says that in the discussions, which 
resumed in Cairo today, the Palestinians stressed that such a 
move is essential to prevent an interim vacuum in the 
territories. 
  [Ya'ari] The talks, which were resumed at Cairo's Shepherd 
Hotel today, are headed by Major General Amnon Shahaq and Dr. 
Nabil Sha'th. Members of both delegations have said that on 23 
February, they may be able to deliver a public statement on the 
results of this round. 
  This time the Civilian Affairs Committee will discuss issues 
such as a fuel excise tax, the manner in which stamps printed by 
Palestinians will be introduced and used, and the Palestinian 
city planning powers. The Security Committee will decide on the 
number of Palestinian police and their equipment. The 
Palestinians want to set up a UN-supervised police training camp 
in the Bethlehem area, but Israel refuses to allow any foreign 
sponsorship. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

