<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel Rejects Jordan's Request To Discuss Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2002060594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 20 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2002060594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the bilateral talks in Washington, Israel has 
rejected Jordan's request to discuss the border between the two 
countries. The Israeli delegation was instructed by the 
government to turn down the request. According to Israel, the 
matter should only be discussed when the two sides come up with 
a draft for a peace agreement between Israel and Jordan. Talks 
on the Israel-Jordan track will resume Tuesday [22 February] and 
will focus on security arrangements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

