<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-035 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Criticizes Rabin's Deadline Proposal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2002205594 Amman Jordan Television Network in English 2000 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2002205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News At Ten"] </F>
  [Text] Palestine President Yasir 'Arafat once again accused 
Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin of prevaricating on 
Palestinian autonomy. 
  Speaking to reporters upon arrival in Amman today, President 
'Arafat criticized Rabin for suggesting a delay in the April 
13th deadline for Israel's withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho. 
  He said he was astonished by Rabin's insistence not to 
implement the PLO-Israeli accord accurately and honestly. 
  [Begin recording] ['Arafat] I am completely astonished why 
he 
is insisting not to follow up and not to implement accurately 
and honestly what had been agreed upon. 
  [Unidentified reporter] When do you expect to sign the 
agreement on the self-rule? 
  ['Arafat] What he is saying is that he is trying to bypass 
what had been agreed upon. 
  [Reporter] When do you expect to be back in Jericho? 
  ['Arafat] We have to wait and see. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

