<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Abbas Comments on Time Factor in Peace Process </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2002202894 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 20 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2002202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Mahmud 'Abbas, Abu Mazin, PLO Executive 
Committee member, has said that the time element favors neither 
the Palestinians nor the peace process. As time goes by 
frustration and despondency grow ever deeper, 'Abbas observed. 
  In remarks published in Manama today, he said the 
Palestinian-Israeli peace accord must be based on clear 
guidelines rather than on theory. He blamed the delay in 
implementing the agreement on all kinds of details raised by 
Israel. Such tactics, he said, call the final results into 
question. 
  He indicated that once agreement is reached on the broad 
outlines, it will be easy to tackle problems on the ground. 
  Asked about Israel's position on the Palestinian state, 
Abu-Mazin said the Palestinian state is a certainty. He called 
on Israel to honor the 13 April deadline for Israel's pullout 
from Gaza and Jericho. Unless the deadline is met, the 
Palestinian-Israeli agreement is likely to come to nothing, he 
stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

