<H3> <TI>   Al-Husayni, Others Reject Israeli Protection Offer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1802122694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1158 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1802122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 18 Feb (MENA)--Citing informed Palestinian 
sources in Jerusalem, the Tunisian newspaper AL-SABAH reports 
that Faysal al-Husayni and several other Palestinian leaders 
inside the occupied territories have rejected an Israeli offer 
to provide them with police guards. The Israeli authorities 
warned the Palestinian leaders that they might be attacked by 
members of fanatical Jewish organizations. 
  The Palestinians sources said the warning was repeated 
following the recent progress in the Palestinian-Israeli 
negotiations and the imminent implementation of the transitional 
period. 
  The sources pointed out that Israeli rightist groups and 
parties are very critical of the statements made by al-Husayni 
and other figures pertaining to the Palestinian determination to 
establish a Palestinian state that has its capital in Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

