<H3> <TI>   Hamas Movement Rejects Dialogue With Israel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2102180794 Damascus SANA in Arabic 1715 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2102180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus SANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, 21 Feb (SANA)--The Palestinian Hamas 
Movement has reiterated its rejection of the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement and all its annexes because they represent dangerous 
concessions and humiliating submission to the Israeli occupation. 
  In a statement today, the movement said it rejects any 
dialogue between Hamas and Israel, saying the only language the 
Israeli enemy understands will remain the language of force and 
struggle, not the language of concessions and capitulation. 
  The statement said that all the Israeli attempts to open 
dialogue with Hamas members detained in Israeli prisons have 
failed, and will never be successful. 

</TEXT>

