<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Qian Qichen, Chinese vice premier and foreign 
minister, has said that Pakistan-China friendship is useful for 
and conducive to the maintenance of peace and stability in Asia. 
Talking to newsmen on his arrival in Islamabad yesterday 
evening, he expressed the hope that his visit will further 
promote the existing friendship between Pakistan and the PRC and 
expand the understanding between the two countries. He said 
that the Chinese Government sincerely wishes further expansion 
of cooperation between the two countries. Foreign Minister 
Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, who received the Chinese foreign minister 
at the airport, stressed the need for regular exchange of views 
between the two countries so as to further strengthen their 
bilateral relations. 

