<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Kill Ari'el Resident in Ambush </TI></H3>
<H4>   IDF Imposes Curfew </H4>
<F P=102> TA1902053294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 19 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1902053294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Terrorists last night shot and killed a woman 
resident of the Samaria town of Ari'el. The attack took place 
as she was traveling with her husband and two children near the 
village of Qarawat Bani-Hasan west of Ari'el. Two bursts of 
fire were directed from a stationary vehicle. The woman, whose 
name has not yet been released, was hit in the head. Her 
husband did not stop the car, and rushed to a nearby Army base, 
from where she was evacuated by ambulance to Beilinson Hospital 
in Petah Tiqva. She died soon after. Our reporter says she was 
in the fifth month of pregnancy. 
  At the site of the attack, the casings of Kalashnikov 
bullets 
were found. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] has imposed a 
curfew on the area, and a hunt is on for the terrorists. 

</TEXT>

