<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Kill Ari'el Resident in Ambush </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hamas Claims Responsibility </H4>
<F P=102> TA1902111994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 19 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1902111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] has claimed 
responsibility for the attack on the trans-Samaria highway, that 
killed Tzipora Sason from Ari'el. Our correspondent Moti Amir 
reports that graffiti sprayed in the Ramallah area said the 
'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam squad had perpetrated the attack. 
[Reporting on Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0905 on 19 
February, Amir adds that a Hamas leaflet faxed to the radio 
station and signed by 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam also claimed 
responsibility for the attack.] 
  Our correspondent further reports that after the attack, the 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] detained several men suspected of 
participating in the act or possessing knowledge about the 
perpetrators. 
  Tzipora Sason was shot by two rounds fired from a parked 
vehicle at the car in which she was traveling with her husband 
and two children. She was hit in the head and abdomen, and she 
died of her wounds. 
  Our correspondent notes that Major General Dani Yatom, the 
Central Command commander, and Major General Sha'ul Mufaz, the 
IDF regional commander, are overseeing the investigation on the 
site of the attack. 
  Reacting to the attack, Likud Chairman Binyamin Netanyahu 
said the government should beef up the IDF deployment in the 
area and launch an offensive on terrorists, rather than 
preoccupy itself with withdrawal. 
  Tzomet Chairman Refa'el Eytan told our correspondent Hayim 
Hecht that the IDF should clamp a curfew on all the Arab 
villages along the trans-Samaria highway and maintain it until 
the murderers are apprehended. 
  Moledet leader Knesset Member Rehav'am Ze'evi called on the 
government to provide Jews residing in Judaea, Samaria, and Gaza 
with full protection. 
  [Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew at 0900 GMT on 19 February 
adds 
that reacting to the attack, the YI'UD [Independent and 
Democratic Israel] faction said all Hamas activists suspected of 
terrorist activity should be deported, and a closure should be 
imposed on Arab population centers in the territories."] 

</TEXT>

