Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In the territories last night, an IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] soldier was lightly wounded by terrorist gunfire 
near Rafah in the Gaza Strip. The attack took place near the 
border between Rafah and Egypt, when machine-gun fire was 
directed at an Army jeep patrolling in the area. Army troops 
returned the fire, and two residents of Rafah were injured. 
  Meanwhile, in the center of Hebron, a bomb was set off last 
night on one of the main streets. It exploded but caused no 
injuries or damage. 
  Settlers in the territories are now blocking roads in 
protest 
over the murder of Tzipora Sason, the 30-year old woman from 
Ari'el who was shot by terrorists last Friday night. At the 
site of one of the roadblocks is reporter Mark Weiss: 
  [Begin recording] Groups of settlers at five locations 
throughout the West Bank set up roadblocks at 5 o'clock this 
morning. Coordinated by the YESHA' [Judaea, Samaria, and the 
Gaza Strip] settlers council, the protesters burned tires and 
threatened to turn back Arab vehicles; however, nearly all Arab 
cars turned back before reaching the settlers' roadblocks or, as 
in the past, planned to wait till 7 o'clock before traveling on 
the roads, knowing that the demonstrations end at 7 o'clock. 
[passage omitted] 
  Large numbers of soldiers and police are on hand, but so far 
there have been no confrontations, and the security forces have 
decided not to disperse the settlers and to allow the protests 
to continue. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

