<H3> <TI>   `Terrorists' Kill Ari'el Resident in Ambush </TI></H3>
<H4>   Rabin Comments </H4>
<F P=102> TA2002055594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 20 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2002055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] In many places in Israel 
there were demonstrations yesterday to protest the murder of 
Tzipora Sason. Our military affairs correspondent Karmela 
Menashe reports that the security forces are continuing the 
manhunt in search of the murderers, but so far without any 
results. The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] will beef up its 
presence in the Trans-Samaria highway and adjacent areas. A 
senior military source told our correspondent that over the last 
few months security presence has been increased along the 
Trans-Samaria highway, but there are dozens of Arab villages on 
both sides of the road, and this makes it hard to prevent 
attacks. 
  Some 25-28 wanted men from the rejectionist front 
organizations and Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] are active 
In Judaea and Samaria, as well as three 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam 
squads. 
  Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin said that the Palestinian 
detainees who participated in terror attacks will not be 
released. He emphasized that first the problem of the Israeli 
MIA's must be solved, as well as that of the inhabitants of the 
territories who have aided Israel -- only then will Israel 
discuss the release of the Palestinian detainees. 
  Over the last few days the Palestinian representatives 
negotiating with Israel have said that unless it is ensured that 
all the Palestinian detainees are released, they will not sign 
the full agreement with Israel. 

</TEXT>

