<H3> <TI>   Serbian Military Team Visits, To Discuss Air Raids </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1902144894 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People in Arabic 
1400 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1902144894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The regime of tyrant Saddam Husayn has strengthened 
its relations with the Serbian regime in former Yugoslavia. At 
the invitation of 'Ali Hasan al-Majid, the Iraqi regime's 
defense minister, a team of Serbian military experts recently 
arrived in Baghdad to exchange information and discuss the 
results of air raids against Iraq during the Gulf war. A 
Bosnian military source said the military and political 
similarity between the two regimes pushed them toward 
rapprochement and coordination. 

</TEXT>

