<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Collapse Threatens `Suicidal Popular Uprising' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2002153394 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People in Arabic 
1400 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2002153394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi People </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Reliable reports from Baghdad yesterday said that 
gradually and cautiously evolving developments threaten a 
suicidal popular uprising to be led this time by hungry Iraqis 
who, thanks to soaring prices of essential commodities and an 
all-time low Iraqi dinar, find it hard to survive. The reports 
said the Iraqi people are effectively on the threshold of a 
mammoth revolution to express their anger with the unjust 
regime, which is primarily responsible for the people's bitter 
suffering today. 
  The reports said a state of extreme tension and anxiety 
prevail in the streets of Baghdad and the governorates in 
anticipation of possible developments in the next few days if 
the economic deterioration and collapse continue and hunger, 
want, and destitution affecting the overwhelming majority of 
citizens sharpen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

